thread.title: Fifth Third meets 2Q profit forecasts

title: Fifth Third meets 2Q profit forecasts
text:
Tip : Use comma (,) to separate multiple quotes. Learn more... 
Tue, Jul 21, 2015, 12:23 BST - UK Markets close in 4 hrs 7 mins Fifth Third meets 2Q profit forecasts Fifth Third Bancorp meets 2Q net income expectations, misses revenue forecasts Associated Press – 27 minutes ago 
CINCINNATI (AP) -- Fifth Third Bancorp (FITB) on Tuesday reported second-quarter net income of $315 million. 
The bank, based in Cincinnati, said it had earnings of 36 cents per share. 
The results matched Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of 14 analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was also for earnings of 36 cents per share. 
The regional bank posted revenue of $1.44 billion in the period, which fell short of Street forecasts. Nine analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $1.47 billion. 
Fifth Third shares have risen slightly more than 4 percent since the beginning of the year, while the Standard & Poor's 500 index has increased slightly more than 3 percent. The stock has declined 1 percent in the last 12 months.
